<li id="cite_note-Richelson-pg296-11">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Richelson-pg296_11-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Richelson-pg296_11-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Richelson <i>Op. Cit</i>, page 296.</li>
<li id="cite_note-CIA-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CIA_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class=""><i><a href="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB190/03.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB190/03.pdf" rel="nofollow">The 22 September 1979 Event</a></i>, Interagency Intelligence Memorandum, <a href="/wiki/National_Security_Archive" title="National Security Archive">National Security Archive</a>, December 1979, pp.&#160;11 (paragraph 41), MORI DocID: 1108245<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB190/03.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB190/03.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB190/03.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2006-11-01</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+22+September+1979+Event&amp;rft.date=December+1979&amp;rft.series=Interagency+Intelligence+Memorandum&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B11+%28paragraph+41%29&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNational+Security+Archive%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gwu.edu%2F%7Ensarchiv%2FNSAEBB%2FNSAEBB190%2F03.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Vela_Incident"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-SNIE-4-1-74-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-SNIE-4-1-74_13-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class=""><i><a href="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB240/snie.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB240/snie.pdf" rel="nofollow">Prospects for Further Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons</a></i>, Special National Intelligence Estimate, <a href="/wiki/CIA" title="CIA" class="mw-redirect">CIA</a>, 23 August 1974, SNIE 4-1-74<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB240/snie.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB240/snie.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB240/snie.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2008-01-20</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Prospects+for+Further+Proliferation+of+Nuclear+Weapons&amp;rft.date=23+August+1974&amp;rft.series=Special+National+Intelligence+Estimate&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BCIA%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gwu.edu%2F%7Ensarchiv%2FNSAEBB%2FNSAEBB240%2Fsnie.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Vela_Incident"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/science/09bomb.html?pagewanted=2" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/09/science/09bomb.html?pagewanted=2" rel="nofollow">Hidden Travels of the Atomic Bomb</a> Book Review <i>New York Times</i> December 8, 2008</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Richelson <i>Op. Cit</i>, chapter seven, "The Double Flash".</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.un.org/documents/sc/res/1977/scres77.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.un.org/documents/sc/res/1977/scres77.htm" rel="nofollow">UNSCR 418 of 4 November 1977: States should refrain from "any co-operation with South Africa in the manufacture and development of nuclear weapons"</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.foia.cia.gov/" class="external text" title="http://www.foia.cia.gov/" rel="nofollow">Trends in South Africa's Nuclear Security Policies and Programs</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.foia.cia.gov/" class="external text" title="http://www.foia.cia.gov/" rel="nofollow">The Dynamics of Nuclear Proliferation: Balance of Incentives and Constraints</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> David Albright, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=VAwAAAAAMBAJ&amp;pg=PA1&amp;source=gbs_toc_pages&amp;cad=0_1#PPA37,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=VAwAAAAAMBAJ&amp;pg=PA1&amp;source=gbs_toc_pages&amp;cad=0_1#PPA37,M1" rel="nofollow">'South Africa and the affordable bomb'</a>, <a href="http://www.thebulletin.org" class="external text" title="http://www.thebulletin.org" rel="nofollow">Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists</a>, July/August 1994.</li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> Associated Press, archived at <a href="http://www.nuclearweaponarchive.org/Israel/Isrsa497.txt" class="external text" title="http://www.nuclearweaponarchive.org/Israel/Isrsa497.txt" rel="nofollow">nuclearweaponarchive.org</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/world/israel/nuke-test.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/world/israel/nuke-test.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/world/israel/nuke-test.htm</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> Albuquerque Journal, 11 July, archived at <a href="http://nuclearweaponarchive.org/Safrica/Vela.html" class="external text" title="http://nuclearweaponarchive.org/Safrica/Vela.html" rel="nofollow">nuclearweaponarchive.org</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://rpc.senate.gov/_files/100799Unverifiable.pdf" class="external text" title="http://rpc.senate.gov/_files/100799Unverifiable.pdf" rel="nofollow">Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty Cannot Be Verified</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
<ul>
<li>Aviation Week &amp; Space Technology/July 21, 1997 page 33 "Admission of 1979 Nuclear Test Finally Validates Vela Data" by William B. Scott/Colorado Springs</li>
</ul>
